Name: Epic Kao Rune
Types: Rune
Components: Greater Kao Rune, Level 4 Spell Slot
Description: This rune symbolizes ill intent, lasting suffering, and misfortune. It is commonly known as the rune of curses, allowing those who wield it the ability to inflict calamity upon their foes.SPACESPACEWhile wearing or using an item imbued with this rune, you gain the following feature.SPACECurse of SpeedSPACEAs an action, you attempt to curse a target within DISTANCE30-45DISTANCE feet of you. The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be forced to take the Dash action on their turns for the next TIME1-3TIME rounds, expending all of their available movement if possible. A creature that succeeds on its saving throw is immune to this effect for the next 24 hours.SPACESPACECurse of IllnessSPACEAs an action, you inflict horrible disease upon a target within DISTANCE30-45DISTANCE feet of you. The target must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or become poisoned for TIME3-5TIME rounds. While poisoned, they take an additional DAMAGE3-4DAMAGEd6 poison damage whenever they take damage. A creature that succeeds on its saving throw is immune to this effect for the next 24 hours.SPACESPACECurse of RegretSPACEAs an action, you attempt to curse a target within DISTANCE30-45DISTANCE feet of you with terrible regret. The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be cursed for TIME3-5TIME rounds. For the duration, whenever the target makes an attack against a creature they must take the Help action as a bonus action, helping the creature they targeted. A creature that succeeds on its saving throw is immune to this effect for the next 24 hours.SPACESPACECurse of DeathSPACEAs an action, you attempt to curse a target within DISTANCE30-45DISTANCE feet of you with inexorable awareness of their own mortality. The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw, or become cursed for TIME3-5TIME rounds. While cursed, the target becomes frightened of all creatures it can see, and you can use a reaction to deal DAMAGE3-5DAMAGEd6 necrotic damage to the target at the start of each of its turns. A creature that succeeds on its saving throw is immune to this effect for the next 24 hours.SPACESPACEYou may use this rune a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus before its magic is depleted. The rune will recharge from ambient magic as you complete a long rest.
